.TH FIX-ARCH-PGP 1 "2026-02-14" "v1.1.1" "Arch Linux Utilities"

.SH NAME
fix-arch-pgp \- professional Arch Linux pacman PGP repair utility

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fix-arch-pgp
.RI [ options ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fix-arch-pgp
is a professional command-line utility designed to detect and repair
pacman PGP signature errors, corrupted package issues, and mirror inconsistencies
on Arch Linux systems.

It provides automatic keyring reset, optional mirror optimization,
safe detection mode, logging, and dry-run capability.

All operations are logged to:

    /var/log/fix-arch-pgp.log

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.B --quick
Run minimal ultra-fast repair mode.
Skips key refresh step for faster execution.

.TP
.B --dry-run
Show commands without executing them.
Useful for auditing or automation preview.

.TP
.B --force
Skip confirmation prompt before performing system modifications.

.TP
.B --auto-detect
Check system for signature errors before performing repair.
If no issue is detected, the tool exits safely without changes.

.TP
.B --version
Display version information.

.TP
.B --info
Display detailed project metadata including:
version, creation date, author, license, install path, and log location.

.SH LOGGING
All executed commands and output are recorded in:

    /var/log/fix-arch-pgp.log

.SH DEPENDENCIES
Requires:
    pacman
    gnupg

Optional:
    reflector (for mirror optimization)

.SH EXAMPLES

Full repair:

    fix-arch-pgp

Quick repair:

    fix-arch-pgp --quick

Auto detect and repair if needed:

    fix-arch-pgp --auto-detect

Dry run:

    fix-arch-pgp --dry-run

Force execution without prompt:

    fix-arch-pgp --force

